{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868104300,"sessionID":"ses_286037c4dffe1uedSL24Jhd5aN","part":{"id":"prt_d79fcc789001IE7wFyxopix10W","messageID":"msg_d79fcad2a001QBckpX63fwRQlo","sessionID":"ses_286037c4dffe1uedSL24Jhd5aN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-095fbb60a6ce40b1b1a76d695d0e9828","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) |\n8: | Module | `cmd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Shared CLI Infrastructure (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/version.go` with version constants\n20:   - Define `Version = \"0.1.0\"`\n21:   - Define `GitCommit` (populated at build time)\n22:   - Define `BuildDate` (populated at build time)\n23:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/version.go`\n24:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n25: \n26: - [ ] **T1.2**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go` with common flag handling\n27:   - Define `FlagSet` struct for common CLI flags\n28:   - Include `Verbose`, `Kubeconfig`, `Namespace` flags\n29:   - Define `BindFlags(fs *flag.FlagSet)` method\n30:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go`\n31:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.3**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go` with klog initialization\n34:   - Define `InitLogging(verbose bool)` function\n35:   - Call `klog.InitFlags(nil)` and set `logtostderr=true`\n36:   - Set verbose level based on flag\n37:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go`\n38:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T1.4**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go` with signal handling\n41:   - Define `SetupSignalHandler() context.Context`\n42:   - Handle SIGTERM, SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n43:   - Return cancelable context\n44:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go`\n45:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n46: \n47: ### Phase 2: agentcube CLI Binary (ST-2)\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `cmd/agentcube/main.go` skeleton\n50:   - Package: `main`\n51:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentcube`\n52:   - Define `main()` function\n53:   - Setup flag parsing with common flags\n54:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n55:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentcube`\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `--version` flag handling in agentcube\n58:   - Add `-v`, `--version` flag\n59:   - Print version info: `AgentCube CLI version: {Version}, commit: {GitCommit}`\n60:   - Exit 0 after printing version\n61:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n62:   - Verification: `./bin/agentcube --version`\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement agentcube subcommand structure\n65:   - Define subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n66:   - Use `flag.NewFlagSet` for each subcommand\n67:   - Print usage help on invalid subcommand\n68:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n69:   - Verification: `./bin/agentcube --help`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.4**: Add agentcube help and usage documentation\n72:   - Define command help text\n73:   - Implement `printUsage()` function\n74:   - Add example usage in help output\n75:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n76:   - Verification: `./bin/agentcube`\n77: \n78: ### Phase 3: agentd Daemon Binary (ST-3)\n79: \n80: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `cmd/agentd/main.go` skeleton\n81:   - Package: `main`\n82:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentd`\n83:   - Define `main()` function\n84:   - Setup flag parsing\n85:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n86:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define agentd configuration flags\n89:   - `--port` (int, default 8081): HTTP listening port\n90:   - `--router-url` (string): Router service URL\n91:   - `--workload-manager-url` (string): WorkloadManager URL\n92:   - `--idle-cleanup-interval` (duration, default 1m): Cleanup interval\n93:   - `--idle-timeout` (duration, default 15m): Session idle timeout\n94:   - `--kubeconfig` (string): Kubernetes config path\n95:   - `--namespace` (string, default \"default\"): Kubernetes namespace\n96:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n97:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T3.3**: Initialize agentd dependencies\n100:   - Create Kubernetes client from kubeconfig\n101:   - Initialize Redis/Valkey store client\n102:   - Create `SandboxLifecycleManager` instance\n103:   - Create `IdleCleanupController` instance\n104:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n105:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n106: \n107: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement agentd server startup\n108:   - Call `IdleCleanupController.Start()`\n109:   - Setup signal handler for graceful shutdown\n110:   - Wait for shutdown signal\n111:   - Call `IdleCleanupController.Stop()` on exit\n112:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n113:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentd -v`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T3.5**: Add agentd version flag\n116:   - Add `--version` flag\n117:   - Print version and exit\n118:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n119:   - Verification: `./bin/agentd --version`\n120: \n121: ### Phase 4: agentsandbox Runtime Binary (ST-4)\n122: \n123: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go` skeleton\n124:   - Package: `main`\n125:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentsandbox`\n126:   - Define `main()` function\n127:   - Follow pattern from `cmd/picod/main.go`\n128:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n129:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define agentsandbox configuration flags\n132:   - `--port` (int, default 8080): HTTP listening port\n133:   - `--workspace` (string): Workspace directory path\n134:   - `--session-id` (string): Current session ID\n135:   - `--sandbox-id` (string): Sandbox identifier\n136:   - `--entrypoint` (string): Agent entrypoint command\n137:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n138:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.3**: Integrate agentsandbox with picod package\n141:   - Import `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod`\n142:   - Create `picod.Config` from flags\n143:   - Create `picod.NewServer(config)`\n144:   - Call `server.Run(ctx)`\n145:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n146:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement agentsandbox graceful shutdown\n149:   - Setup signal handler (SIGTERM, SIGINT)\n150:   - Pass cancelable context to server\n151:   - Log shutdown message\n152:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n153:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentsandbox -v`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T4.5**: Add agentsandbox version flag\n156:   - Add `--version` flag\n157:   - Print version and exit\n158:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n159:   - Verification: `./bin/agentsandbox --version`\n160: \n161: ### Phase 5: agentctl Control Tool Binary (ST-5)\n162: \n163: - [ ] **T5.1**: Create `cmd/agentctl/main.go` skeleton\n164:   - Package: `main`\n165:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentctl`\n166:   - Define `main()` function\n167:   - Setup flag parsing\n168:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n169:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T5.2**: Define agentctl global flags\n172:   - `--kubeconfig` (string): Kubernetes config path\n173:   - `--namespace` (string, default \"default\"): Kubernetes namespace\n174:   - `--output` (string, default \"table\"): Output format (table, json, yaml)\n175:   - `--verbose` (bool): Enable verbose output\n176:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n177:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement agentctl `list` subcommand\n180:   - List all AgentRuntime CRs in namespace\n181:   - Output: name, status, endpoint, age\n182:   - Support table/json/yaml output formats\n183:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n184:   - Verification: `./bin/agentctl list --namespace=default`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement agentctl `get` subcommand\n187:   - Get specific AgentRuntime by name\n188:   - Show detailed status information\n189:   - Support json/yaml output\n190:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n191:   - Verification: `./bin/agentctl get my-agent`\n192: \n193: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement agentctl `delete` subcommand\n194:   - Delete AgentRuntime by name\n195:   - Support `--force` flag for immediate deletion\n196:   - Support `--wait` flag to wait for deletion\n197:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n198:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n199: \n200: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement agentctl `status` subcommand\n201:   - Check session status for an agent\n202:   - Show active sessions count\n203:   - Show last activity time\n204:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n205:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n206: \n207: - [ ] **T5.7**: Add agentctl version flag and help\n208:   - Add `--version` flag\n209:   - Print version and exit\n210:   - Implement usage help\n211:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n212:   - Verification: `./bin/agentctl --version`\n213: \n214: ### Phase 6: Build Configuration (ST-6)\n215: \n216: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create Makefile with build targets\n217:   - `build-agentcube`: Build agentcube binary\n218:   - `build-agentd`: Build agentd binary\n219:   - `build-agentsandbox`: Build agentsandbox binary\n220:   - `build-agentctl`: Build agentctl binary\n221:   - `build-all`: Build all binaries\n222:   - File: `Makefile`\n223:   - Verification: `make build-all`\n224: \n225: - [ ] **T6.2**: Add ldflags for version injection\n226:   - `-X main.Version=$(VERSION)`\n227:   - `-X main.GitCommit=$(GIT_COMMIT)`\n228:   - `-X main.BuildDate=$(BUILD_DATE)`\n229:   - File: `Makefile`\n230:   - Verification: `make build-agentcube && ./bin/agentcube --version`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T6.3**: Create Dockerfile for each binary\n233:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentcube\n234:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentd\n235:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentsandbox\n236:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentctl\n237:   - File: `build/Dockerfile.agentcube`, `build/Dockerfile.agentd`, etc.\n238:   - Verification: `docker build -f build/Dockerfile.agentcube -t agentcube .`\n239: \n240: - [ ] **T6.4**: Add install target in Makefile\n241:   - `install`: Copy binaries to `/usr/local/bin`\n242:   - Support `PREFIX` variable for custom install path\n243:   - File: `Makefile`\n244:   - Verification: `make install PREFIX=/tmp/test && /tmp/test/bin/agentcube --version`\n245: \n246: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n247: \n248: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test agentcube CLI version output\n249:   - Test: `--version` flag prints correct version format\n250:   - Test: exits with code 0\n251:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main_test.go`\n252:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentcube -run TestVersion -v`\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test agentcube CLI help output\n255:   - Test: `--help` prints usage information\n256:   - Test: invalid subcommand shows help\n257:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main_test.go`\n258:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentcube -run TestHelp -v`\n259: \n260: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test agentd daemon startup\n261:   - Test: flags parsed correctly\n262:   - Test: dependencies initialized\n263:   - Test: server startup succeeds (mocked)\n264:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main_test.go`\n265:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentd -v`\n266: \n267: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test agentsandbox runtime startup\n268:   - Test: flags parsed correctly\n269:   - Test: picod server created\n270:   - Test: graceful shutdown works\n271:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main_test.go`\n272:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentsandbox -v`\n273: \n274: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test agentctl control commands\n275:   - Test: `list` command output format\n276:   - Test: `get` command output format\n277:   - Test: `delete` command with flags\n278:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main_test.go`\n279:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentctl -v`\n280: \n281: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test signal handling in all binaries\n282:   - Test: SIGTERM triggers graceful shutdown\n283:   - Test: SIGINT triggers graceful shutdown\n284:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/signal_test.go`\n285:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/internal/cli -v`\n286: \n287: ### Phase 8: Integration & Validation (ST-8)\n288: \n289: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify all binaries build successfully\n290:   - `go build ./cmd/agentcube`\n291:   - `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n292:   - `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n293:   - `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n294:   - File: `cmd/`\n295:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/...`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify binary names and paths\n298:   - Binaries output to `bin/` directory\n299:   - Names: `agentcube`, `agentd`, `agentsandbox`, `agentctl`\n300:   - File: `Makefile`\n301:   - Verification: `make build-all && ls -la bin/`\n302: \n303: - [ ] **T8.3**: Run all cmd tests with coverage\n304:   - `go test ./cmd/... -v` passes\n305:   - Coverage: >70% for cmd packages\n306:   - File: `cmd/`\n307:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/... -cover`\n308: \n309: - [ ] **T8.4**: Lint and vet verification\n310:   - `go vet ./cmd/...` passes\n311:   - `golangci-lint run ./cmd/...` passes\n312:   - File: `cmd/`\n313:   - Verification: `go vet ./cmd/... && golangci-lint run ./cmd/...`\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T8.5**: Verify Makefile targets\n316:   - `make build-all` succeeds\n317:   - `make test` succeeds\n318:   - `make install` succeeds\n319:   - File: `Makefile`\n320:   - Verification: `make build-all test`\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## Task Dependencies\n325: \n326: ```\n327: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3 → T1.4\n328:                     ↓\n