{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868129590,"sessionID":"ses_286037c4dffe1uedSL24Jhd5aN","part":{"id":"prt_d79fd2e2d001KLaCeklkKC950n","messageID":"msg_d79fd1bab001q0aEfRcvbkIWjK","sessionID":"ses_286037c4dffe1uedSL24Jhd5aN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-99cbe318b0174f3885d49d42583c33f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-019 |\n8: | Module | cmd |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: 实现 4 个 CLI 二进制入口，提供 agentcube 项目的命令行工具集，作为 Kubernetes-native sandbox 编排平台的运维和管理接口。\n17: \n18: **Current State**: 项目已有 `cmd/picod/main.go` 作为 Sandbox Pod 内的 Pico daemon 入口，但缺少以下关键入口：\n19: - 主管理 CLI 工具\n20: - Agent daemon 入口\n21: - WorkloadManager HTTP 服务入口\n22: - 运维控制工具\n23: \n24: **Target State**: 创建 4 个独立二进制入口:\n25: 1. `cmd/agentcube/` — 主 CLI 工具（统一入口点，聚合子命令）\n26: 2. `cmd/agentd/` — Agent daemon 入口（运行 idle cleanup controller）\n27: 3. `cmd/agentsandbox/` — Sandbox 运行时入口（WorkloadManager HTTP 服务）\n28: 4. `cmd/agentctl/` — 控制工具入口（运维管理、调试工具）\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n33: \n34: ### 2.1 In Scope\n35: \n36: | Deliverable | Description |\n37: |-------------|-------------|\n38: | `cmd/agentcube/main.go` | 主 CLI 二进制入口，提供版本、状态检查等基础命令 |\n39: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Agent daemon 二进制入口，启动 idle cleanup controller |\n40: | `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go` | Sandbox 运行时二进制入口，启动 WorkloadManager HTTP Server |\n41: | `cmd/agentctl/main.go` | 控制工具二进制入口，提供运维管理命令 |\n42: | 单元测试 | 各入口的基础测试 |\n43: \n44: ### Implementation Details\n45: \n46: #### `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n47: ```go\n48: package main\n49: \n50: import (\n51:     \"flag\"\n52:     \"fmt\"\n53:     \"os\"\n54: )\n55: \n56: var (\n57:     version   = \"dev\"\n58:     showVersion = flag.Bool(\"version\", false, \"Show version information\")\n59: )\n60: \n61: func main() {\n62:     flag.Parse()\n63:     if *showVersion {\n64:         fmt.Printf(\"agentcube version: %s\\n\", version)\n65:         os.Exit(0)\n66:     }\n67:     fmt.Println(\"agentcube - Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform\")\n68:     fmt.Println(\"Usage: agentcube [command]\")\n69:     fmt.Println(\"Commands:\")\n70:     fmt.Println(\"  agentd       Run agent daemon (idle cleanup controller)\")\n71:     fmt.Println(\"  agentsandbox Run sandbox runtime (WorkloadManager)\")\n72:     fmt.Println(\"  agentctl     Control and management tool\")\n73:     os.Exit(1)\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: #### `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n78: ```go\n79: package main\n80: \n81: import (\n82:     \"context\"\n83:     \"flag\"\n84:     \"os\"\n85:     \"os/signal\"\n86:     \"syscall\"\n87:     \"time\"\n88: \n89:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n90:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n91:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n92: )\n93: \n94: func main() {\n95:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n96:     \n97:     interval := flag.Duration(\"interval\", agentd.DefaultIdleCleanupInterval, \"Cleanup check interval\")\n98:     idleTimeout := flag.Duration(\"idle-timeout\", agentd.DefaultIdleTimeout, \"Idle session timeout\")\n99:     flag.Parse()\n100: \n101:     store := workloadmanager.NewMemoryStore()\n102:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient()\n103:     if err != nil {\n104:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n105:     }\n106:     \n107:     lifecycleConfig := workloadmanager.DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n108:     lifecycleManager := workloadmanager.NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, lifecycleConfig, klog.NewKlogr())\n109:     \n110:     ctrl := agentd.NewIdleCleanupController(store, lifecycleManager, *interval, *idleTimeout, klog.NewKlogr())\n111:     \n112:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n113:     defer cancel()\n114:     \n115:     ctrl.Start()\n116:     klog.Info(\"agentd started\")\n117:     \n118:     sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n119:     signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n120:     <-sigCh\n121:     \n122:     ctrl.Stop()\n123:     klog.Info(\"agentd stopped\")\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: #### `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n128: ```go\n129: package main\n130: \n131: import (\n132:     \"context\"\n133:     \"flag\"\n134:     \"os\"\n135:     \"os/signal\"\n136:     \"syscall\"\n137: \n138:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n139:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n140: )\n141: \n142: func main() {\n143:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n144:     \n145:     addr := flag.String(\"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n146:     flag.Parse()\n147: \n148:     cfg := workloadmanager.DefaultConfig()\n149:     cfg.Addr = *addr\n150: \n151:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient()\n152:     if err != nil {\n153:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n154:     }\n155:     \n156:     store := workloadmanager.NewMemoryStore()\n157:     \n158:     server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(cfg, klog.NewKlogr(), k8sClient, store)\n159:     server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n160:     server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(store, k8sClient))\n161:     \n162:     server.GracefulShutdown()\n163:     \n164:     errCh := server.Start()\n165:     klog.InfoS(\"agentsandbox started\", \"addr\", *addr)\n166:     \n167:     select {\n168:     case err := <-errCh:\n169:         klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n170:     case sig := <-waitSignal():\n171:         klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n172:         server.Stop(context.Background())\n173:     }\n174: }\n175: \n176: func waitSignal() chan os.Signal {\n177:     sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n178:     signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n179:     return sigCh\n180: }\n181: ```\n182: \n183: #### `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n184: ```go\n185: package main\n186: \n187: import (\n188:     \"flag\"\n189:     \"fmt\"\n190:     \"os\"\n191: \n192:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n193: )\n194: \n195: func main() {\n196:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n197:     flag.Parse()\n198: \n199:     args := flag.Args()\n200:     if len(args) == 0 {\n201:         printUsage()\n202:         os.Exit(1)\n203:     }\n204: \n205:     switch args[0] {\n206:     case \"list\":\n207:         fmt.Println(\"list: list all sandboxes (TODO)\")\n208:     case \"delete\":\n209:         fmt.Println(\"delete: delete a sandbox (TODO)\")\n210:     case \"status\":\n211:         fmt.Println(\"status: show sandbox status (TODO)\")\n212:     default:\n213:         printUsage()\n214:         os.Exit(1)\n215:     }\n216: }\n217: \n218: func printUsage() {\n219:     fmt.Println(\"agentctl - AgentCube control tool\")\n220:     fmt.Println(\"Usage: agentctl [command]\")\n221:     fmt.Println(\"Commands:\")\n222:     fmt.Println(\"  list     List all sandboxes\")\n223:     fmt.Println(\"  delete   Delete a sandbox by session ID\")\n224:     fmt.Println(\"  status   Show sandbox status\")\n225: }\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n229: \n230: | Item | Reason |\n231: |------|--------|\n232: | Cobra/Viper 命令行框架集成 | 保持初始实现简单，使用标准 flag 包 |\n233: | agentctl 完整功能实现 | 仅提供框架，功能在后续 AR 中添加 |\n234: | 配置文件支持 | 使用命令行参数，配置文件在后续 AR 中添加 |\n235: | Docker/容器镜像构建 | 由 CI/CD 系统处理 |\n236: | Helm chart 更新 | 由部署 AR 处理 |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n241: \n242: ### 3.1 新增文件\n243: \n244: ```\n245: cmd/\n246: ├── agentcube/\n247: │   └── main.go          # 主 CLI 入口\n248: ├── agentd/\n249: │   └── main.go          # Agent daemon 入口\n250: ├── agentsandbox/\n251: │   └── main.go          # WorkloadManager 入口\n252: ├── agentctl/\n253: │   └── main.go          # 控制工具入口\n254: └── picod/\n255: │   └── main.go          # (existing) Pico daemon\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n259: \n260: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n261: |------------|---------|--------|\n262: | `pkg/agentd` | existing | `cmd/agentd` 直接依赖 IdleCleanupController |\n263: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | existing | `cmd/agentsandbox` 和 `cmd/agentd` 依赖 HTTPServer、K8sClient |\n264: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | 所有二进制使用统一日志框架 |\n265: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.31.0 | K8sClient 初始化需要 K8s 配置 |\n266: \n267: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n268: \n269: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n270: |----------|--------------|\n271: | Docker 镜像 | 每个二进制打包为独立镜像或多阶段镜像入口 |\n272: | Helm chart | 作为 deployment 配置的容器入口点 |\n273: | CI/CD pipeline | Go build targets 更新以包含新二进制 |\n274: \n275: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n276: \n277: - 无破坏性变更，纯新增功能\n278: - 不影响现有 `cmd/picod/main.go` 代码\n279: - `pkg/` 包 API 保持不变\n280: \n281: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n282: \n283: - 所有二进制遵循 Kubernetes 命令行约定：`flag.Parse()` + klog 初始化\n284: - 信号处理：支持 SIGTERM/SIGINT 优雅关闭\n285: - 环境变量：后续可扩展 KUBECONFIG、NAMESPACE 环境变量支持\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n290: \n291: ### Alternative 1: 单一统一二进制 + 子命令\n292: \n293: **Approach**: 只创建一个 `agentcube` 二进制，所有功能作为子命令 (`agentcube daemon`, `agentcube sandbox`, `agentcube ctl`)\n294: \n295: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n296: |--------|------------|\n297: | Pros | 单一镜像、分发简单；统一版本管理；cobra/spf13 框架成熟 |\n298: | Cons | 容器部署场景需要全部依赖；不同服务无法独立版本/扩展；镜像体积增大 |\n299: \n300: **Decision**: 未采纳。Kubernetes 生态普遍使用独立二进制（如 kubelet、kube-proxy），便于容器化部署和资源隔离。\n301: \n302: ### Alternative 2: 使用 Cobra 命令行框架\n303: \n304: **Approach**: 使用 `spf13/cobra` + `spf13/viper` 构建命令行框架\n305: \n306: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n307: |--------|------------|\n308: | Pros | 功能丰富、自动生成帮助文档、支持子命令嵌套、配置文件集成 |\n309: | Cons | 增加依赖复杂度；当前功能简单不需要复杂框架 |\n310: \n311: **Decision**: 部分采纳。主 CLI `agentcube` 和 `agentctl` 可在后续 AR 中集成 Cobra，daemon 类二进制保持简单 flag 模式。\n312: \n313: ### Alternative 3: 二进制作为 Library 入口\n314: \n315: **Approach**: 在 `pkg/` 中实现可导入的 `Run()` 函数，`cmd/` 仅调用\n316: \n317: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n318: |--------|------------|\n319: | Pros | 代码可测试性更好；入口点清晰分离；便于其他项目集成 |\n320: | Cons | 需要重构现有包结构；增加抽象层 |\n321: \n322: **Decision**: 采纳。参考 `cmd/picod/main.go` 模式，保持 `pkg/` 包提供 Server/Controller 对象，`cmd/` 仅负责初始化和启动。\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## 5. Risks\n327: \n328: | Risk | Mitigation |\n329: |------|------------|\n330: | K8s 客户端初始化失败导致服务不可用 | 使用 InClusterConfig + fallback；提供 --kubeconfig 参数 |\n331: | agentd idle cleanup controller 与 WorkloadManager GC 冲突 | 明确职责边界：agentd 处理 session idle，WM GC 处理 K8s 资源 |\n332: | 二进制构建目标遗漏 | 在 Makefile/go.mod 中明确列出所有 cmd/ 入口 |\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n337: \n338: 1. **Phase 1: 搭建框架**\n339:    - [x] 确认现有 pkg 包结构 (agentd, workloadmanager, router)\n340:    - [ ] 创建 cmd/agentcube/main.go 基础框架\n341:    - [ ] 创建 cmd/agentd/main.go 基础框架\n342:    - [ ] 创建 cmd/agentsandbox/main.go 基础框架\n343:    - [ ] 创建 cmd/agentctl/main.go 基础框架\n344: \n345: 2. **Phase 2: 实现入口**\n346:    - [ ] 实现 agentd 入口：集成 IdleCleanupController\n347:    - [ ] 实现 agentsandbox 入口：集成 HTTPServer + Handlers\n348:    - [ ] 实现 agentctl 入口：基础命令框架\n349:    - [ ] 实现 agentcube 入口：版本展示 + 命令指南\n350: \n351: 3. **Phase 3: 测试**\n352:    - [ ] 单元测试：各入口 flag 解析、初始化逻辑\n353:    - [ ] 集成测试：agentd 启动/停止流程\n354:    - [ ] 集成测试：agentsandbox HTTP 服务启动\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ## 7. References\n359: \n360: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client-go 生成代码规范\n361: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` — IdleCleanupController 实现\n362: - `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — HTTPServer 实现\n363: - `cmd/picod/main.go` — 现有二进制入口参考模式\n364: - `project.md` — AgentCube 项目架构和约定\n\n(End of file - total 364 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-019 |\n| Module | cmd |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\n实现 4 个 CLI 二进制入口，提供 agentcube 项目的命令行工具集，作为 Kubernetes-native sandbox 编排平台的运维和管理接口。\n\n**Current State**: 项目已有 `cmd/picod/main.go` 作为 Sandbox Pod 内的 Pico daemon 入口，但缺少以下关键入口：\n- 主管理 CLI 工具\n- Agent daemon 入口","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775868129564,"end":1775868129588}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868129594,"sessionID":"ses_286037c4dffe1uedSL24Jhd5aN","part":{"id":"prt_d79fd310c001DbZTqe5lt9tHHl","messageID":"msg_d79fd1bab001q0aEfRcvbkIWjK","sessionID":"ses_286037c4dffe1uedSL24Jhd5aN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e77b99eca2a64f35ac1621d35da49812","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement CLI binary entry points for four core AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Agentd, Router, and picod. Each binary provides a `main.go` entry point that initializes logging, parses command-line flags, constructs configuration, and launches the respective server/controller.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: workloadmanager binary entry point\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Workload Manager server at `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: workloadmanager imports\n22: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading imports\n24: - **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n25:   - `context` for server lifecycle\n26:   - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n27:   - `os` for exit handling\n28:   - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` for server implementation\n29:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: workloadmanager flag definitions\n32: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n33: - **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n34: - **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n35:   - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n36:   - `kubeconfig` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Kubeconfig path (empty for in-cluster)\"`)\n37:   - `namespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Namespace to watch (empty for all)\"`)\n38:   - `redisAddr` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis address\"`)\n39:   - `redisPassword` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis password\"`)\n40:   - `sshUsername` (`string`, default `\"sandbox\"`, description `\"SSH username for sandbox access\"`)\n41:   - `sshPort` (`int`, default `22`, description `\"SSH port for sandbox access\"`)\n42:   - `runtimeClassName` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Runtime class name for pods\"`)\n43:   - `metricsPort` (`int`, default `8081`, description `\"Metrics port\"`)\n44:   - `enableLeaderElection` (`bool`, default `false`, description `\"Enable leader election\"`)\n45:   - `leaderElectionNamespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Leader election namespace\"`)\n46:   - `leaderElectionID` (`string`, default `\"workloadmanager\"`, description `\"Leader election ID\"`)\n47:   - `syncPeriod` (`duration`, default `30s`, description `\"Sync period for informers\"`)\n48:   - `concurrentReconciles` (`int`, default `5`, description `\"Concurrent reconcile workers\"`)\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: workloadmanager klog initialization\n51: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n52: - **WHEN** `main()` starts\n53: - **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n54: - AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: workloadmanager flag parsing\n57: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n58: - **WHEN** `flag.Parse()` is called\n59: - **THEN** all defined flags SHALL be parsed and available\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: workloadmanager config construction\n62: - **GIVEN** parsed flags\n63: - **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n64: - **THEN** `pkg/workloadmanager.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n65:   - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n66:   - `Kubeconfig`: from `--kubeconfig` flag\n67:   - `Namespace`: from `--namespace` flag (or in-cluster namespace via fieldRef if empty)\n68:   - `RedisAddr`: from `--redisAddr` flag (or env `REDIS_ADDR`)\n69:   - `RedisPassword`: from `--redisPassword` flag (or env `REDIS_PASSWORD`)\n70:   - `SSHUsername`: from `--sshUsername` flag\n71:   - `SSHPort`: from `--sshPort` flag\n72:   - `RuntimeClassName`: from `--runtimeClassName` flag\n73:   - `MetricsPort`: from `--metricsPort` flag\n74:   - `EnableLeaderElection`: from `--enableLeaderElection` flag\n75:   - `LeaderElectionNamespace`: from `--leaderElectionNamespace` flag\n76:   - `LeaderElectionID`: from `--leaderElectionID` flag\n77:   - `SyncPeriod`: from `--syncPeriod` flag\n78:   - `ConcurrentReconciles`: from `--concurrentReconciles` flag\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: workloadmanager server creation\n81: - **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n82: - **WHEN** calling `pkg/workloadmanager.NewServer(config)`\n83: - **THEN** server instance SHALL be created\n84: - AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n85: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: workloadmanager server run\n88: - **GIVEN** successful server creation\n89: - **WHEN** calling `server.Run(context.Background())`\n90: - **THEN** server SHALL start and block until termination\n91: - AND if run fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n92: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: workloadmanager graceful shutdown\n95: - **GIVEN** `server.Run` receives SIGTERM/SIGINT\n96: - **WHEN** context is cancelled\n97: - **THEN** server SHALL gracefully shut down\n98: - AND all controllers SHALL stop reconciling\n99: - AND `klog.Info(\"shutting down workload manager\")` SHALL be called\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: agentd binary entry point\n104: \n105: The system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Agent Daemon at `cmd/agentd/main.go`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: agentd imports\n108: - **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n109: - **WHEN** reading imports\n110: - **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n111:   - `context` for server lifecycle\n112:   - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n113:   - `os` for exit handling\n114:   - `os/signal` for signal handling\n115:   - `syscall` for signal types\n116:   - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd` for agent daemon implementation\n117:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: agentd flag definitions\n120: - **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n121: - **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n122: - **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n123:   - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n124:   - `workspace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Workspace directory path\"`)\n125:   - `kubeconfig` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Kubeconfig path\"`)\n126:   - `namespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Namespace for agent sandbox\"`)\n127:   - `redisAddr` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis address\"`)\n128:   - `redisPassword` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis password\"`)\n129:   - `routerURL` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Router URL for session routing\"`)\n130:   - `workloadManagerURL` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Workload Manager URL\"`)\n131:   - `idleTimeout` (`duration`, default `15m`, description `\"Idle timeout for sessions\"`)\n132:   - `maxSessionDuration` (`duration`, default `8h`, description `\"Maximum session duration\"`)\n133:   - `verbose` (`bool`, default `false`, description `\"Enable verbose logging\"`)\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: agentd klog initialization\n136: - **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n137: - **WHEN** `main()` starts\n138: - **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n139: - AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: agentd config construction\n142: - **GIVEN** parsed flags\n143: - **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n144: - **THEN** `pkg/agentd.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n145:   - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n146:   - `Workspace`: from `--workspace` flag (current directory if empty)\n147:   - `Kubeconfig`: from `--kubeconfig` flag\n148:   - `Namespace`: from `--namespace` flag\n149:   - `RedisAddr`: from `--redisAddr` flag (or env `REDIS_ADDR`)\n150:   - `RedisPassword`: from `--redisPassword` flag (or env `REDIS_PASSWORD`)\n151:   - `RouterURL`: from `--routerURL` flag\n152:   - `WorkloadManagerURL`: from `--workloadManagerURL` flag\n153:   - `IdleTimeout`: from `--idleTimeout` flag\n154:   - `MaxSessionDuration`: from `--maxSessionDuration` flag\n155:   - `Verbose`: from `--verbose` flag\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: agentd daemon creation\n158: - **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n159: - **WHEN** calling `pkg/agentd.NewDaemon(config)`\n160: - **THEN** daemon instance SHALL be created\n161: - AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create agentd: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n162: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: agentd daemon run\n165: - **GIVEN** successful daemon creation\n166: - **WHEN** calling `daemon.Run(ctx)`\n167: - **THEN** daemon SHALL start HTTP server and background controllers\n168: - AND signal handler SHALL wait for SIGTERM/SIGINT\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: agentd signal handling\n171: - **GIVEN** running daemon\n172: - **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n173: - **THEN** context SHALL be cancelled\n174: - AND `klog.Info(\"received shutdown signal\")` SHALL be called\n175: - AND daemon SHALL stop gracefully\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: router binary entry point\n180: \n181: The system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Router at `cmd/router/main.go`.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: router imports\n184: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go`\n185: - **WHEN** reading imports\n186: - **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n187:   - `context` for server lifecycle\n188:   - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n189:   - `os` for exit handling\n190:   - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` for router implementation\n191:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: router flag definitions\n194: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go`\n195: - **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n196: - **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n197:   - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n198:   - `debug` (`bool`, default `false`, description `\"Enable debug mode\"`)\n199:   - `redisAddr` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis address\"`)\n200:   - `redisPassword` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis password\"`)\n201:   - `workloadManagerURL` (`string`, default `\"http://workloadmanager:8080\"`, description `\"Workload Manager URL\"`)\n202:   - `namespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Namespace to operate in\"`)\n203:   - `metricsPort` (`int`, default `8081`, description `\"Metrics port\"`)\n204:   - `sessionTimeout` (`duration`, default `15m`, description `\"Session timeout\"`)\n205:   - `maxSessionDuration` (`duration`, default `8h`, description `\"Maximum session duration\"`)\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: router klog initialization\n208: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go`\n209: - **WHEN** `main()` starts\n210: - **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n211: - AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: router config construction\n214: - **GIVEN** parsed flags\n215: - **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n216: - **THEN** `pkg/router.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n217:   - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n218:   - `Debug`: from `--debug` flag\n219:   - `RedisAddr`: from `--redisAddr` flag (or env `REDIS_ADDR`)\n220:   - `RedisPassword`: from `--redisPassword` flag (or env `REDIS_PASSWORD`)\n221:   - `WorkloadManagerURL`: from `--workloadManagerURL` flag (or env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n222:   - `Namespace`: from `--namespace` flag (or env `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`)\n223:   - `MetricsPort`: from `--metricsPort` flag\n224:   - `SessionTimeout`: from `--sessionTimeout` flag\n225:   - `MaxSessionDuration`: from `--maxSessionDuration` flag\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: router server creation\n228: - **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n229: - **WHEN** calling `pkg/router.NewServer(config)`\n230: - **THEN** router server SHALL be created\n231: - AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create router: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n232: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: router server run\n235: - **GIVEN** successful router creation\n236: - **WHEN** calling `server.Run(context.Background())`\n237: - **THEN** router SHALL start HTTP server\n238: - AND if run fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n239: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: router debug mode logging\n242: - **GIVEN** `--debug` flag is `true`\n243: - **WHEN** router starts\n244: - **THEN** `klog.SetLogger(klog.NewKlogr())` MAY be called with verbose settings\n245: - AND debug-level logs SHALL be emitted\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ### Requirement: picod binary entry point\n250: \n251: The system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for picod (code interpreter daemon) at `cmd/picod/main.go`.\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: picod imports\n254: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n255: - **WHEN** reading imports\n256: - **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n257:   - `context` for server lifecycle\n258:   - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n259:   - `os` for exit handling\n260:   - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` for picod server implementation\n261:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: picod flag definitions\n264: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n265: - **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n266: - **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n267:   - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n268:   - `workspace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Workspace directory path (empty means current directory)\"`)\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: picod klog initialization\n271: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n272: - **WHEN** `main()` starts\n273: - **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n274: - AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: picod config construction\n277: - **GIVEN** parsed flags\n278: - **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n279: - **THEN** `pkg/picod.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n280:   - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n281:   - `Workspace`: from `--workspace` flag\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: picod server creation\n284: - **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n285: - **WHEN** calling `pkg/picod.NewServer(config)`\n286: - **THEN** picod server SHALL be created\n287: - AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n288: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: picod server run\n291: - **GIVEN** successful server creation\n292: - **WHEN** calling `server.Run(context.Background())`\n293: - **THEN** picod SHALL start HTTP server for code execution\n294: - AND if run fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n295: - AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ### Requirement: flag naming conventions\n300: \n301: The system SHALL follow consistent flag naming conventions for all binaries.\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: flag naming style\n304: - **GIVEN** any CLI binary in `cmd/`\n305: - **WHEN** defining flags\n306: - **THEN** flags SHALL use:\n307:   - lowercase names without underscores (e.g., `kubeconfig`, not `kube_config`)\n308:   - descriptive help text\n309:   - sensible defaults matching production requirements\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: flag default behavior\n312: - **GIVEN** flags with empty string defaults\n313: - **WHEN** flag is not provided\n314: - **THEN** code SHALL check for environment variable fallback where applicable\n315: - AND environment variables SHALL use uppercase underscore naming (e.g., `REDIS_ADDR`)\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: environment variable integration\n320: \n321: The system SHALL support environment variable fallback for key configuration options.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Redis configuration from environment\n324: - **GIVEN** `--redisAddr` and `--redisPassword` flags are empty\n325: - **WHEN** binary starts\n326: - **THEN** `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variables SHALL be read\n327: - AND values SHALL populate the respective Config fields\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n330: - **GIVEN** router binary with empty `--workloadManagerURL`\n331: - **WHEN** router starts\n332: - **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable SHALL be read\n333: - AND value SHALL populate Config.WorkloadManagerURL\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Namespace from environment\n336: - **GIVEN** binaries with empty `--namespace`\n337: - **WHEN** running in-cluster\n338: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read\n339: - AND if not set, downward API fieldRef may be used for namespace detection\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: exit codes\n344: \n345: The system SHALL use consistent exit codes across all binaries.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: successful execution\n348: - **GIVEN** binary runs and completes\n349: - **WHEN** no error occurs\n350: - **THEN** process SHALL exit with code `0`\n351: \n352: #### Scenario: initialization failure\n353: - **GIVEN** binary fails to initialize\n354: - **WHEN** `NewServer` or `NewDaemon` returns error\n355: - **THEN** process SHALL exit with code `1`\n356: - AND error SHALL be logged via `klog.Fatalf`\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: runtime failure\n359: - **GIVEN** binary fails during execution\n360: - **WHEN** `Run` returns error\n361: - **THEN** process SHALL exit with code `1`\n362: - AND error SHALL be logged via `klog.Fatalf`\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ### Requirement: Makefile build integration\n367: \n368: The system SHALL integrate with Makefile targets for building binaries.\n369: \n370: #### Scenario: workloadmanager build target\n371: - **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n372: - **WHEN** running `make build`\n373: - **THEN** `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` SHALL be executed\n374: - AND binary SHALL be placed at `bin/workloadmanager`\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: agentd build target\n377: - **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n378: - **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n379: - **THEN** `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` SHALL be executed\n380: - AND binary SHALL be placed at `bin/agentd`\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: router build target\n383: - **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n384: - **WHEN** running `make build-router`\n385: - **THEN** `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` SHALL be executed\n386: - AND binary SHALL be placed at `bin/agentcube-router`\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: build all target\n389: - **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n390: - **WHEN** running `make build-all`\n391: - **THEN** all three binaries SHALL be built (workloadmanager, agentd, agentcube-router)\n392: \n393: ---\n394: \n395: ### Requirement: Dockerfile integration\n396: \n397: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles for containerizing binaries.\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: workloadmanager Dockerfile\n400: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile`\n401: - **WHEN** building image\n402: - **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL compile `./cmd/workload-manager` as `workloadmanager`\n403: - AND runtime SHALL use Alpine 3.19 with user `apiserver` UID 1000\n404: - AND port 8080 SHALL be exposed\n405: \n406: #### Scenario: router Dockerfile\n407: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n408: - **WHEN** building image\n409: - **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL compile `./cmd/router` as `agentcube-router`\n410: - AND runtime SHALL use Alpine 3.19 with user `router` UID 1000\n411: - AND port 8080 SHALL be exposed\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: picod Dockerfile\n414: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n415: - **WHEN** building image\n416: - **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` as `picod`\n417: - AND runtime SHALL use Ubuntu 24.04 with Python3 installed\n418: - AND binary SHALL run as root for sandbox permissions\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: Package structure\n423: \n424: The system SHALL organize cmd files correctly.\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: workloadmanager main.go location\n427: - **GIVEN** repository root\n428: - **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n429: - **THEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` SHALL exist\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: agentd main.go location\n432: - **GIVEN** repository root\n433: - **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n434: - **THEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL exist\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: router main.go location\n437: - **GIVEN** repository root\n438: - **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n439: - **THEN** `cmd/router/main.go` SHALL exist\n440: \n441: #### Scenario: picod main.go location\n442: - **GIVEN** repository root\n443: - **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n444: - **THEN** `cmd/picod/main.go` SHALL exist\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ### Requirement: Unit tests for binary entry points\n449: \n450: The system SHALL have unit tests verifying flag parsing and config construction.\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: TestWorkloadManagerFlagParsing\n453: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main_test.go`\n454: - **WHEN** running tests\n455: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n456:   - Default flag values are correct\n457:   - Custom flag values override defaults\n458:   - Config construction maps flags correctly\n459: \n460: #### Scenario: TestRouterFlagParsing\n461: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main_test.go`\n462: - **WHEN** running tests\n463: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n464:   - Default flag values are correct\n465:   - Debug mode flag is parsed\n466:   - WorkloadManagerURL can be overridden\n467: \n468: #### Scenario: TestAgentdFlagParsing\n469: - **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main_test.go`\n470: - **WHEN** running tests\n471: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n472:   - Default idle timeout is 15 minutes\n473:   - Default max session duration is 8 hours\n474:   - Workspace flag handling\n475: \n476: #### Scenario: TestPicodFlagParsing\n477: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main_test.go`\n478: - **WHEN** running tests\n479: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n480:   - Default port is 8080\n481:   - Workspace flag handling with empty default\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## Constants Summary\n486: \n487: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n488: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n489: | DefaultPort | `8080` | all binaries | Default HTTP listening port |\n490: | DefaultMetricsPort | `8081` | workloadmanager, router | Default metrics port |\n491: | DefaultIdleTimeout | `15m` | agentd | Default idle session timeout |\n492: | DefaultMaxSessionDuration | `8h` | agentd, router | Default maximum session duration |\n493: | DefaultSSHUsername | `\"sandbox\"` | workloadmanager | Default SSH username |\n494: | DefaultSSHPort | `22` | workloadmanager | Default SSH port |\n495: | DefaultSyncPeriod | `30s` | workloadmanager | Default informer sync period |\n496: | DefaultConcurrentReconciles | `5` | workloadmanager | Default reconcile worker count |\n497: \n498: ---\n499: \n500: ## Dependencies Summary\n501: \n502: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n503: |---------|---------|---------|\n504: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Internal | Workload Manager server implementation |\n505: | `pkg/agentd` | Internal | Agent Daemon implementation |\n506: | `pkg/router` | Internal | Router server implementation |\n507: | `pkg/picod` | Internal | picod server implementation |\n508: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n509: | `flag` | Standard | CLI flag parsing |\n510: | `context` | Standard | Server lifecycle management |\n511: | `os` | Standard | Exit handling |\n512: | `os/signal` | Standard | Signal handling (agentd) |\n513: | `syscall` | Standard | Signal types (agentd) |\n514: \n515: ---\n516: \n517: ## File Changes Summary\n518: \n519: | File | Action | Description |\n520: |------|--------|-------------|\n521: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Create | Workload Manager binary entry point with flags for port, kubeconfig, redis, SSH, leader election, etc. |\n522: | `cmd/workload-manager/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n523: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Create | Agent Daemon binary entry point with flags for port, workspace, redis, router URL, idle timeout |\n524: | `cmd/agentd/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n525: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Create | Router binary entry point with flags for port, debug, redis, workload manager URL |\n526: | `cmd/router/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n527: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Create | picod binary entry point with flags for port, workspace |\n528: | `cmd/picod/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n529: \n530: ---\n531: \n532: ## References\n533: \n534: - `changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md` — Workload Manager controller implementation\n535: - `changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md` — Agentd idle cleanup controller\n536: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for CR operations\n537: - `deployment/design.md` — Dockerfile patterns and Makefile targets\n538: - `cli-toolkit/design.md` — Python CLI (kubectl-agentcube) reference\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## Validation Checklist\n543: \n544: - [ ] workloadmanager main.go imports klog, flag, context, os\n545: - [ ] workloadmanager flags: port, kubeconfig, namespace, redisAddr, redisPassword, SSH params, leader election, sync period\n546: - [ ] workloadmanager calls NewServer(config) and Run(ctx)\n547: - [ ] agentd main.go imports signal/syscall for graceful shutdown\n548: - [ ] agentd flags: port, workspace, kubeconfig, redis, routerURL, workloadManagerURL, idleTimeout\n549: - [ ] agentd calls NewDaemon(config) and Run(ctx)\n550: - [ ] router main.go flags: port, debug, redisAddr, workloadManagerURL\n551: - [ ] router calls NewServer(config) and Run(ctx)\n552: - [ ] picod main.go flags: port, workspace (minimal)\n553: - [ ] picod calls NewServer(config) and Run(ctx)\n554: - [ ] Environment variable fallback for redisAddr, redisPassword, workloadManagerURL, namespace\n555: - [ ] Exit codes: 0 for success, 1 for failure\n556: - [ ] klog.InitFlags(nil) and logtostderr=true in all binaries\n557: - [ ] Makefile targets: build, build-agentd, build-router, build-all\n558: - [ ] Dockerfiles reference correct cmd paths\n559: - [ ] Package structure: cmd/workload-manager/, cmd/agentd/, cmd/router/, cmd/picod/\n560: - [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing in each binary\n561: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n562: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n563: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 563 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement CLI binary entry points for four core AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Agentd, Router, and picod. Each binary provides a `main.go` entry point that initializes logging, parses command-line flags, constructs configuration, and launches the respective server/controller.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: workloadmanager binary entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Workload Manager server at `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868129569,"end":1775868129591}}}}
